# History: ruff-specific-rule-fixes

This file preserves the full verbatim content of the skills consolidated into
`ruff-specific-rule-fixes.md`, along with the version history of the canonical.

## v1.6.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1434 — D413 missing-blank-after-last-section on new `hephaestus/nats/config.py` docstrings
**Verification:** verified-local (`pixi run ruff check` clean + `pixi run mypy` over 448 source files + 26 unit tests passed locally after the fix; full CI for that PR not yet confirmed at capture time)

### What changed

- Added Pattern G — Fix Ruff D413 (missing blank line after last docstring section), with the exact error text, before/after Google-style docstring snippet, and the `[*]`-autofix command.
- Documented that `ruff format` neither adds nor flags the trailing blank line — only `ruff check` (and `ruff check --fix`) does — so a docstring can pass `ruff format` yet fail `ruff check`.
- Added description trigger (11), four When-to-Use bullets, a Quick Reference command, two Failed Attempts rows, a Results & Parameters subsection, and a ProjectHephaestus issue #1434 Verified On row.
- Added tags: D413, pydocstyle, docstring, google-style, raises-section, trailing-blank-line, ruff-format-vs-check, projecthephaestus.
- Bumped version 1.5.0 -> 1.6.0; date 2026-06-26 -> 2026-06-30.

### Why

The pattern catalog covered S101/C901/RUF022/I001/RUF100/E501/floor-bump violations but not D413. The issue #1434 session showed D413 is a distinct trap: it fires only on a docstring's LAST section and is invisible to `ruff format`, so formatting alone leaves it unfixed. Capturing the `ruff format` vs `ruff check` split and the `[*]`-autofix remedy prevents the same surprise on the next new Google-style docstring.

### Previous version (v1.5.0) snapshot

